02:03.659 --> 02:05.361
[sighs]

02:10.032 --> 02:11.501
You can do this.

02:43.337 --> 02:44.738
[phone ringing]

02:54.115 --> 02:55.716
<i>[answering machine]</i>
<i>You have reached Walter White.</i>

02:55.750 --> 02:57.846
<i>At the tone please state</i>
<i>your name, number,</i>

02:57.966 --> 02:59.199
<i>and the reason for your call.</i>

02:59.234 --> 03:01.402
<i>Thank you.</i>
[machine beeps]

03:01.437 --> 03:02.737
<i>[Skyler, sighing]</i>
<i>Third try.</i>

03:02.771 --> 03:04.773
<i>Walt, if you're there,</i>
<i>please pick up.</i>

03:06.909 --> 03:09.244
<i>Okay. Well, I really wanted</i>
<i>to do this together,</i>

03:09.278 --> 03:11.246
<i>but I can hear him getting up,</i>

03:11.280 --> 03:13.081
<i>and it's not like I can keep</i>
<i>him from seeing the thing,</i>

03:13.116 --> 03:16.251
<i>so I'm sorry, but I've waited</i>
<i>as long as possible,</i>

03:16.286 --> 03:20.442
and I-- I guess I'm going to have
to go ahead without you,

03:20.562 --> 03:23.626
so call me.

03:27.498 --> 03:32.436
Oh. Hey, happy birthday,
sweet sixteen.

03:32.471 --> 03:33.905
Mwah.

03:33.939 --> 03:35.206
[giggles]
Thanks, Mom.

03:35.240 --> 03:37.308
Of course, I thought
you might sleep through it.

03:37.343 --> 03:39.010
Ha ha.
[chuckles]

03:39.045 --> 03:42.848
So since it's almost--
oh, noon,

03:42.882 --> 03:45.250
I think your first
big birthday decision

03:45.284 --> 03:48.086
is breakfast or lunch.

03:48.121 --> 03:49.688
Um, pancakes?

03:49.722 --> 03:52.223
Pancakes it is.

03:52.258 --> 03:54.292
Okay, could you do me a favor?

03:54.327 --> 03:55.360
I forgot to get the paper.

03:55.394 --> 03:56.528
Can you go out
and grab it for me?

03:56.562 --> 03:58.730
Sure.
Thanks.

04:12.013 --> 04:13.447
[Skyler]
Surprise!

04:15.150 --> 04:17.051
It's from me and your dad.

04:17.084 --> 04:18.687
It's pretty slick, huh?

04:19.689 --> 04:21.822
Yeah. Thanks, Mom.

04:21.857 --> 04:24.358
It's-- It's great.

04:25.727 --> 04:28.028
You know, I really did
a lot of research,

04:28.063 --> 04:29.597
and, I don't know,

04:29.631 --> 04:31.165
this car just really
stood out to me.

04:31.200 --> 04:33.668
It's got a ton
of great features--

04:33.702 --> 04:35.703
power everything, solid engine,

04:35.737 --> 04:36.971
It's really roomy,

04:37.005 --> 04:39.940
so you can carpool
with all your friends,

04:39.975 --> 04:41.575
and of course it is safe

04:41.609 --> 04:43.310
because I am still your mother.

04:43.344 --> 04:45.512
Oh, and it has a CD player,

04:45.547 --> 04:47.414
so you can listen to some tunes
while you're cruising around,

04:47.449 --> 04:48.716
so you know what?

04:48.750 --> 04:50.418
Breakfast can wait.

04:50.452 --> 04:52.687
You want to take it for a spin?

04:52.721 --> 04:55.123
Um, m-m-maybe later.

04:55.157 --> 04:57.158
I'm kind of starving.

04:57.192 --> 04:59.161
Yeah, okay.
Well, let's--

04:59.195 --> 05:02.197
let's get those pancakes going.

05:05.035 --> 05:06.168
[intercom beeps]

05:06.203 --> 05:09.304
<i>[Francesca]</i>
<i>Saul? He's here.</i>

05:09.339 --> 05:11.073
Bad idea.

05:11.107 --> 05:12.508
This is a bad idea.

05:12.542 --> 05:13.608
[intercom beeps]

05:13.643 --> 05:14.876
<i>Saul.</i>

05:17.013 --> 05:18.447
Send him in.

05:21.484 --> 05:24.687
Mr. Beneke. Saul Goodman.
Thank you for coming down.

05:26.756 --> 05:28.924
Yeah. Hi.

05:28.958 --> 05:30.292
Have a seat, please.

05:31.661 --> 05:33.829
I--

05:33.863 --> 05:35.631
I don't really understand
why I'm here.

05:35.665 --> 05:37.266
Is it something to do
with my creditors?

05:37.300 --> 05:40.268
Creditors? No.

05:40.303 --> 05:41.970
I'll cut right to the chase.

05:42.005 --> 05:44.373
Mr. Beneke,
I have some bad news.

05:44.408 --> 05:46.042
Uh...

05:46.076 --> 05:47.510
nothing but, lately.

05:47.544 --> 05:49.912
Your great-aunt Birgit
passed away.

05:50.914 --> 05:52.081
I'm sorry, who?

05:52.115 --> 05:53.815
Uh...

05:53.850 --> 05:56.017
Apparently, she passed away

05:56.052 --> 05:57.252
in Diekirch, Luxembourg,

05:57.286 --> 05:59.821
and this was, wow,
eight years ago.

05:59.855 --> 06:01.589
I just assumed
you two were close,

06:01.623 --> 06:02.790
given that--

06:03.892 --> 06:06.560
Well, maybe this is good news.

06:06.594 --> 06:07.628
[chuckles]

06:07.662 --> 06:09.697
Birgit left behind
a sizable estate,

06:09.731 --> 06:13.133
of which you, Mr. Beneke,
are the primary beneficiary.

06:13.168 --> 06:16.670
- What? - Yeah, well, seems she had
no immediate relatives,

06:16.704 --> 06:18.605
so the estate's
just been sitting

06:18.640 --> 06:19.973
while the folks over in the EU

06:20.007 --> 06:22.175
searched for a living heir.

06:23.912 --> 06:28.082
I don't know of any relatives
in Luxembourg,

06:28.117 --> 06:30.118
definitely no one who
would name me in their will.

06:30.153 --> 06:31.353
Huh.

06:33.390 --> 06:34.624
Well...

06:36.594 --> 06:37.928
Ah, here you go.

06:37.963 --> 06:39.463
She left no will,

06:39.498 --> 06:41.933
so that's probably
why it took so long.

06:41.967 --> 06:44.001
They traced the inheritance
through to your father,

06:44.036 --> 06:45.203
but his having passed--

06:45.237 --> 06:46.371
my condolences--

06:46.405 --> 06:48.473
you are the next in line

06:48.508 --> 06:54.581
to the tune
of $621,552.33.

06:59.620 --> 07:01.121
Wow.

07:02.523 --> 07:04.390
[vehicle rumbling]

08:15.730 --> 08:19.633
[speaking Spanish]

09:03.448 --> 09:05.249
Where's the phenylacetic acid?

09:16.995 --> 09:18.429
They synthesize their own.

09:19.764 --> 09:21.365
What?

09:23.135 --> 09:24.869
I don't-- I don't do that.

09:27.707 --> 09:30.709
Look, I get
my phenylacetic acid

09:30.743 --> 09:32.244
from the barrel
with the bee on it.

09:32.278 --> 09:34.347
That's how I know how to do it.

09:52.032 --> 09:53.299
What is he saying?

09:53.334 --> 09:54.468
We're working it out.

09:54.502 --> 09:55.702
[speaking Spanish]

10:02.076 --> 10:06.880
Tell this asshole if he wants to
learn how to make my product,

10:06.914 --> 10:10.083
he's got to do it my way,
the right way.

10:16.491 --> 10:17.691
I speak English.

10:17.725 --> 10:21.061
So you understand
what asshole means.

10:21.095 --> 10:24.997
Now, go get me my
phenylacetic acid, asshole.

10:26.634 --> 10:29.335
How long is it going to take you
to get him what he needs?

10:29.369 --> 10:31.638
I don't know.
I have no idea.

10:31.672 --> 10:34.107
Several hours at least.
I can wait.

10:34.141 --> 10:37.377
Gives us time to talk
about the state of this lab.

10:37.411 --> 10:39.212
Don't you have standards?

10:40.781 --> 10:43.215
I mean, this place
is disgusting.

10:43.249 --> 10:46.050
All right, we're going to scour
every vat, every tank,

10:46.085 --> 10:48.018
every cook surface,

10:48.053 --> 10:51.154
and then we're going to clean up every
possible source of contamination,

10:51.188 --> 10:55.057
and only then we cook.

10:55.092 --> 10:56.492
<i>Â¿Comprende?</i>

10:59.528 --> 11:01.897
Who do you think you are?

11:05.035 --> 11:06.902
I'm the guy
your boss brought here

11:06.937 --> 11:08.804
to show you how it's done,

11:08.839 --> 11:12.274
and if this is how you run
your lab, no wonder.

11:12.308 --> 11:15.144
You're lucky
he hasn't fired your ass.

11:15.178 --> 11:17.480
Now, if you don't want
that to happen,

11:17.514 --> 11:20.449
I suggest you stop whining
like a little bitch

11:20.484 --> 11:22.819
and do what I say.

12:04.233 --> 12:05.734
[buzzing]

12:17.682 --> 12:19.283
[groaning]

12:31.361 --> 12:33.429
[phone ringing]

12:41.720 --> 12:42.987
<i>[Walt answering machine]</i>
<i>You have reached Walter White.</i>

12:43.022 --> 12:44.923
<i>At the tone please state</i>
<i>your name, number,</i>

12:44.957 --> 12:46.191
<i>and the reason for your call.</i>

12:46.225 --> 12:47.826
<i>Thank you.</i>
[machine beeps]

12:47.861 --> 12:49.895
<i>Dad! You there?</i>

12:49.930 --> 12:51.330
<i>I'm outside.</i>

12:51.364 --> 12:52.965
<i>Are you okay?</i>

12:53.000 --> 12:54.834
<i>I know you're home.</i>
<i>Your car is here.</i>

12:54.868 --> 12:56.269
<i>You missed my party,</i>

12:56.303 --> 12:58.705
<i>which feels like something's</i>
<i>gotta be really wrong.</i>

12:58.739 --> 13:01.975
<i>I'm... I'm gonna</i>
<i>have to call 911.</i>

13:02.009 --> 13:03.877
<i>I don't know what else to do.</i>

13:17.590 --> 13:18.790
Dad?

13:21.660 --> 13:25.429
[sighs]
Come in if you're coming in.

13:31.570 --> 13:33.271
What happened to you?

13:35.441 --> 13:37.209
[sighs]

13:37.243 --> 13:39.945
What happened?

13:44.384 --> 13:46.819
I got into a fight.

13:46.853 --> 13:47.953
What do you mean, a fight?

13:47.988 --> 13:49.855
Like, what fight?

13:52.292 --> 13:53.993
Are you going to talk
to me here?

13:55.929 --> 13:58.298
[dialing]
What are you doing?

13:58.332 --> 13:59.599
I'm calling Mom.

13:59.634 --> 14:00.667
Don't do that.

14:02.270 --> 14:05.138
Look, I--

14:05.173 --> 14:07.607
I appreciate
that you're concerned.

14:07.642 --> 14:09.009
I'm fine.

14:17.052 --> 14:21.789
Just do not call your mother.

14:22.991 --> 14:24.725
Why not?

14:26.695 --> 14:28.262
Because...

14:29.764 --> 14:31.198
I was gambling.

14:33.968 --> 14:36.569
If you tell your mother,

14:36.604 --> 14:39.038
God, I just would--

14:39.072 --> 14:41.874
I would never,
never hear the end of it,

14:41.908 --> 14:43.843
so please...

14:49.183 --> 14:51.952
can we just keep this
between us?

14:51.986 --> 14:53.487
Would you do that for me?

14:54.556 --> 14:57.959
Just keep it to yourself.

14:59.562 --> 15:01.262
I don't understand.

15:01.297 --> 15:03.165
How'd you get into a fight?

15:03.199 --> 15:05.133
And with who?

15:12.441 --> 15:13.575
[weeping]

15:20.082 --> 15:21.749
I made a mistake.

15:29.493 --> 15:31.393
And it's my own fault.

15:37.399 --> 15:38.566
I had it coming.

15:38.600 --> 15:41.803
Dad, it's okay.

15:44.773 --> 15:47.475
It's all my fault.

15:50.212 --> 15:54.850
I just-- I'm sorry.

15:59.456 --> 16:01.023
I'm sorry.

16:01.058 --> 16:03.159
Dad...

16:03.193 --> 16:04.627
come here.

16:06.162 --> 16:09.898
Come on.
Dad, it's okay.

16:09.932 --> 16:12.900
[sobbing]
Hey-- Hey--

16:12.935 --> 16:15.236
It's okay.

16:15.270 --> 16:17.070
Please, it's--
it's okay.

16:17.105 --> 16:18.672
Look at me.
Look at me.

16:19.674 --> 16:20.841
It's okay.

16:20.875 --> 16:23.010
It is.
Come on.

16:23.044 --> 16:24.712
Come on.

16:32.889 --> 16:35.056
It's okay.

16:39.796 --> 16:44.333
Hey, how was your birthday?

16:45.869 --> 16:48.704
Good.
Get some rest.

16:48.738 --> 16:49.905
Okay.

16:52.876 --> 16:54.309
The new car?

16:55.979 --> 16:58.580
Did you drive it here?

16:58.614 --> 16:59.581
Yeah.

16:59.615 --> 17:00.682
Hm.

17:01.684 --> 17:03.518
Hm.

17:03.553 --> 17:05.020
[sedated]
That's good.

17:06.355 --> 17:07.955
You like it?

17:09.858 --> 17:12.361
Uh, sure.

17:12.395 --> 17:14.063
I do.

17:15.299 --> 17:17.099
It drives great.

17:18.469 --> 17:20.804
That's good, Jesse.

19:35.803 --> 19:37.437
[beeping]

19:37.472 --> 19:39.406
[growls] Yes.

19:40.541 --> 19:41.774
Well done.

19:45.213 --> 19:46.480
First of many.

19:49.417 --> 19:51.118
Yeah?

19:51.152 --> 19:52.252
What's that mean?

19:52.287 --> 19:53.353
You're staying.

19:53.388 --> 19:55.188
You belong to the cartel now.

20:03.801 --> 20:05.801
You can't come
to my work like this.

20:05.836 --> 20:07.469
You're too recognizable.

20:07.504 --> 20:09.505
Your face is plastered

20:09.539 --> 20:12.675
on every bus bench
within a 5-mile radius.

20:12.709 --> 20:14.644
Celebrities have
to get their cars washed,

20:14.678 --> 20:16.712
just like everybody else.

20:16.746 --> 20:19.315
Look, I wouldn't have come
if it wasn't important.

20:19.349 --> 20:21.316
Okay?
What is it?

20:21.351 --> 20:24.953
I went ahead and met
with your Mr. Beneke,

20:24.987 --> 20:29.257
which I will say again,
loudly and for the record, bad idea.

20:29.291 --> 20:33.127
Yes, but it is better
than prison. Correct?

20:33.161 --> 20:34.461
Marginally,

20:34.496 --> 20:36.830
which is why I disbursed
the funds as you requested.

20:36.865 --> 20:38.332
All right, good.

20:38.367 --> 20:40.835
Yeah, I can't believe
he actually bought it--

20:40.869 --> 20:42.470
"Great-aunt Birgit."

20:42.505 --> 20:45.107
What?
But you called it.

20:45.141 --> 20:47.610
I guess people see those zeroes
dance before their eyes,

20:47.644 --> 20:49.112
it's kind
of like highway hypnosis.

20:49.146 --> 20:50.213
All right,
so what's the problem?

20:50.247 --> 20:52.215
Let's just say you and I

20:52.249 --> 20:54.317
don't wear the same
rose-colored glasses

20:54.351 --> 20:56.486
where Johnny Fabulous
is concerned,

20:56.520 --> 20:58.087
so I kept an eye
on his bank accounts,

20:58.121 --> 20:59.822
and I pulled his credit report.

20:59.856 --> 21:02.958
If you would,
note the time on that.

21:06.296 --> 21:10.567
3:54 p.m. yesterday.

21:10.601 --> 21:12.536
Three hours
after leaving my office.

21:12.570 --> 21:15.940
He bought a Mercedes SL550.

21:15.974 --> 21:18.343
He's actually leasing it,
but he put 4,500 down.

21:18.377 --> 21:20.078
He's going to pay
1,830 a month--

21:20.112 --> 21:21.546
fully loaded.

21:21.581 --> 21:23.548
I mean, he even got
the heated steering wheel,

21:23.583 --> 21:25.484
but that's upwards of 6,300

21:25.519 --> 21:28.421
that won't be going to the IRS.

21:28.455 --> 21:29.589
I just thought
you might like to know,

21:29.623 --> 21:32.926
loath as I am to say
I told you so.

21:38.900 --> 21:40.134
Where is he now?

22:07.295 --> 22:08.462
[chuckles]

22:24.979 --> 22:26.680
[sighs]

22:38.828 --> 22:39.994
Hey.

22:40.996 --> 22:42.930
[groans]

22:44.066 --> 22:45.399
How you doing?

22:48.203 --> 22:49.937
Good.

22:57.512 --> 22:59.480
How are you?

23:01.049 --> 23:04.753
I'm fine, but your mother
is going to be worried sick.

23:06.655 --> 23:07.956
I called her last night.

23:11.327 --> 23:15.163
I told her I was spending
the night at Louis'.

23:15.197 --> 23:17.231
It's cool.

23:17.266 --> 23:21.703
So h-h-how are you?

23:24.773 --> 23:26.240
I'm fine, son.

23:26.274 --> 23:27.475
I--

23:31.046 --> 23:32.379
I--

23:34.082 --> 23:38.585
I took these painkillers

23:38.620 --> 23:40.620
that I had left over
from my surgery,

23:40.655 --> 23:43.490
and I made
the brilliant decision

23:43.525 --> 23:45.892
to wash them down
with a couple of beers.

23:48.329 --> 23:51.397
Not my most sterling moment,
I admit,

23:51.432 --> 23:54.800
but I'm fine.

23:55.802 --> 23:58.204
I wish I could take back
last night.

23:58.238 --> 24:00.406
It was your birthday.
This shouldn't be on your mind.

24:00.441 --> 24:02.074
It's okay.

24:02.109 --> 24:03.242
No, it's not okay.

24:03.277 --> 24:04.844
I'm your father,

24:04.878 --> 24:06.613
and I don't want

24:06.647 --> 24:09.082
last night to be--

24:09.116 --> 24:14.054
I mean, you really--

24:14.088 --> 24:17.257
you can't think of me like...

24:18.759 --> 24:20.094
Like what?

24:23.932 --> 24:27.101
I don't understand.

24:39.381 --> 24:41.749
My father died when I was 6.

24:41.783 --> 24:42.983
You knew that, right?

24:43.018 --> 24:44.218
Yeah.

24:47.055 --> 24:49.023
He had Huntington's Disease.

24:49.057 --> 24:51.926
It's--

24:51.960 --> 24:55.397
destroys portions of the brain,

24:55.431 --> 24:58.867
affects muscle control,
leads to dementia.

24:58.901 --> 25:01.102
It's just a nasty disease.

25:01.137 --> 25:03.305
It's genetic.

25:03.339 --> 25:05.473
It terrified my mother
that I might have it,

25:05.507 --> 25:08.977
so they ran tests on me
when I was a kid,

25:09.012 --> 25:10.745
but I came up clean.

25:12.481 --> 25:18.487
My father fell very ill
when I was 4 or 5.

25:18.521 --> 25:20.355
He spent a lot of time
in the hospital.

25:21.958 --> 25:23.525
My--

25:25.394 --> 25:26.728
[chuckles]

25:26.762 --> 25:29.297
My mother would tell me
so many stories

25:29.331 --> 25:31.766
about my father.

25:31.801 --> 25:33.735
She would talk about him
all the time.

25:35.271 --> 25:38.072
I knew about his personality,

25:38.107 --> 25:40.008
how he treated people.

25:40.042 --> 25:42.143
I even knew how he liked
his steaks cooked--

25:42.177 --> 25:43.411
medium rare.

25:43.445 --> 25:45.279
[both chuckle]
Just like you.

25:47.749 --> 25:51.319
I knew things about my father.

25:51.353 --> 25:52.887
I had a lot of information.

25:52.921 --> 25:56.690
It's because people
would tell me these things.

25:56.724 --> 26:00.227
They would paint this picture

26:00.261 --> 26:03.631
of my father for me,

26:03.665 --> 26:05.800
and I always pretended

26:05.834 --> 26:08.403
that was who I saw, too,

26:08.437 --> 26:09.804
who I remembered,

26:09.839 --> 26:12.207
but it was a lie.

26:12.242 --> 26:19.315
In truth, I only have one real,
actual memory of my father.

26:22.719 --> 26:25.487
It must've been
right before he died.

26:25.521 --> 26:28.222
My mother would take me
to the hospital to visit him,

26:28.257 --> 26:31.292
and I remember
the smell in there,

26:31.326 --> 26:32.660
the chemicals.

26:32.694 --> 26:35.429
It was as if they use up

26:35.464 --> 26:38.032
every single cleaning product
they could find

26:38.066 --> 26:39.667
in a 50-mile radius...

26:41.237 --> 26:44.106
like they didn't want you
smelling the sick people.

26:45.842 --> 26:47.576
Oh, there was this stench

26:47.610 --> 26:49.111
of Lysol and bleach.

26:49.145 --> 26:51.146
You could just feel it
coating your lungs.

26:52.249 --> 26:56.719
Anyway, there,
lying on the bed,

26:56.753 --> 26:58.221
is my father.

27:00.891 --> 27:04.559
He's all--
He's all twisted up.

27:07.597 --> 27:13.335
And my mom,
she puts me on her lap.

27:13.369 --> 27:14.937
She's sitting
on the bed next to him

27:14.971 --> 27:17.839
so I can get
a good look at him...

27:19.041 --> 27:21.543
but really he just scares me...

27:25.014 --> 27:27.682
and he's looking right at me...

27:29.651 --> 27:33.253
but I can't even be sure
that he knows who I am.

27:38.827 --> 27:41.028
And your grandmother

27:41.062 --> 27:42.696
is talking,

27:42.730 --> 27:46.833
trying to be cheerful,
you know, as she does,

27:46.868 --> 27:49.936
but the only thing
I could remember

27:49.971 --> 27:52.940
is him breathing.

27:55.243 --> 27:57.411
Oh, th-- this--

27:59.513 --> 28:03.182
this rattling sound,

28:03.217 --> 28:06.919
like if you were shaking
an empty spray-paint can.

28:06.953 --> 28:08.420
Huh?

28:13.192 --> 28:15.560
Like there was nothing in him.

28:20.966 --> 28:22.267
Anyway...

28:25.505 --> 28:29.341
